<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EC) No 718/1999 of 29 March 1999 on a Community-fleet capacity policy to promote inland waterway transport </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 718/1999, mis k&auml;sitleb &uuml;henduse laevastiku mahutavuse poliitikat siseveetranspordi edendamiseks 29. m&auml;rts 1999 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and inparticular Article 75 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 75, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission(1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee(2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 189c of theTreaty(3), </inglise>
<eesti> tegutsedes asutamislepingu artiklis 189c s&auml;testatud korras, (3) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas Regulation (EEC) No 1101/89(4) introduced arrangements forstructural improvements in the inland waterway sector for the fleets operatingon the linked inland waterway networks of Belgium, Germany, France, Luxembourg, the Netherlands and Austria; whereas the objective of that Regulation was toreduce overcapacity in the inland waterway fleets by means of vessel-scrappingschemes coordinated at Community level; whereas that Regulation expires on 28April 1999; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1101/89 (4) kehtestati siseveetranspordi sektori struktuurilise t&auml;iustamise kord laevastikele, mis tegutsevad Belgia, Prantsusmaa, Saksamaa, Luksemburgi ja Madalamaade &uuml;ksteisega &uuml;henduses olevates siseveeteede v&otilde;rgus; selle m&auml;&auml;ruse eesm&auml;rgiks on v&auml;hendada siseveeteede laevastike &uuml;lemahutavust laevade vanametalliks lammutamise kavade kaudu, mis on &uuml;henduse tasandil koosk&otilde;lastatud; nimetatud m&auml;&auml;rus kaotab kehtivuse 28. aprillil 1999; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas of the measures to support these structural improvementarrangements with the aim of avoiding aggravation of existing overcapacity orthe emergence of further overcapacity, the "old-for-new" rule has provedindispensable to balanced operation of the inland waterway market; whereas thisrule also remains an essential instrument for intervention in the event of aserious disturbance on the same market, as defined in Article 1 of Directive96/75/EC(5); whereas steps should be taken to prevent the benefits from thescrapping schemes conducted since 1990 being wiped out by new capacity cominginto service as soon as the abovementioned rule ends; whereas it is thereforeencessary to retain the "old-for-new" rule for a limited period of not morethan four years while gradually reducing the ratios to zero to safeguard thetransition and end the Community market intervention stage; whereas it is alsoimportant to maintain the "old-for-new" instrument for regulating the capacityof the Community fleets beyond these four years, but as a standby mechanism setat zero which could be reactivated only in the event of serious marketdisturbance of the kind referred to in Article 7 of Directive 96/75/EC; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) nimetatud struktuurit&auml;iustuskorra tugimeetmete hulgas, mille eesm&auml;rk on v&auml;ltida olemasoleva &uuml;lemahutavuse suurenemist v&otilde;i uue &uuml;lemahutavuse tekkimist, on reegel "vana uue vastu" siseveeturu tasakaalustatud toimimise seisukohast h&auml;davajalikuks osutunud; nimetatud reegel j&auml;&auml;b ka p&otilde;hiliseks sekkumisvahendiks direktiivi 96/75/E&Uuml; (5) artiklis 1 m&auml;&auml;ratletud t&otilde;siste h&auml;irete korral k&otilde;nealusel turul; tuleks v&otilde;tta meetmeid, et takistada alates 1990. aastast rakendatavatest vanametalliks lammutamise koosk&otilde;lastatud kavadest saadud kasude kaotamist lisamahutavuse t&otilde;ttu, mis v&otilde;etakse kasutusele kohe p&auml;rast eespool nimetatud reegli kohaldamise l&otilde;ppemist; seet&otilde;ttu on vaja, et reegel "vana uue vastu" kehtiks teatava piiratud aja jooksul kestusega k&otilde;ige rohkem neli aastat, mille v&auml;ltel j&auml;rk-j&auml;rgult v&auml;hendatakse suhtarve nullini, et tagada &uuml;leminek ja l&otilde;petada sekkumine &uuml;henduse turul; "vana uue vastu" meetme s&auml;ilitamine on t&auml;htis ka selleks, et reguleerida &uuml;henduse laevastiku mahutavust nende nelja aasta v&auml;ltel, kuid nii, et see oleks nulltasemel toetusmehhanism, mida v&otilde;ib uuesti rakendada &uuml;ksnes direktiivi 96/75/E&Uuml; artiklis 7 nimetatud t&otilde;siste turuh&auml;irete korral; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Whereas the emergence of new overcapacity must be kept in check effectivelyin every branch of the inland waterway transport market; whereas it istherefore important that the measures to be adopted should be generallyapplicable and cover all cargo vessels and pusher craft; whereas there shouldbe exemption from such measures for vessels which, because they operate solelyon closed national or international markets, in no way contribute to theovercapacity on the network of linked inland waterways and provision should bemade for the possibility of exempting vessels which, because their deadweighttonnage is less than 450 tonnes, also do not contribute to such overcapacity; whereas, by contrast, private fleets performing own-account operations cannotbe excluded because of their impact on transport markets; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) uue &uuml;lemahutavuse tekkimine tuleb k&otilde;ikides siseveetranspordi harudes t&otilde;husa kontrolli all hoida; seet&otilde;ttu on t&auml;htis, et vastuv&otilde;etavad meetmed oleksid &uuml;ldkohaldatavad ja h&otilde;lmaksid k&otilde;iki kaubalaevu ja t&otilde;ukurpuksiire; nende meetmete kohaldamisel tuleks teha erand laevadele, mis seet&otilde;ttu, et nad tegutsevad &uuml;ksnes suletud siseriiklikel v&otilde;i rahvusvahelistel turgudel, ei p&otilde;hjusta &uuml;helgi viisil &uuml;lemahutavust &uuml;ksteisega &uuml;henduses olevate siseveeteede v&otilde;rgus, ning tuleks ette n&auml;ha erandi tegemise v&otilde;imalus laevadele, mis seet&otilde;ttu, et nende t&auml;ielik kandev&otilde;ime on alla 450 tonni, samuti ei p&otilde;hjusta nimetatud &uuml;lemahutavust; omal kulul vedusid tegevaid eralaevastikke ei saa seevastu k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse reguleerimisalast v&auml;lja j&auml;tta nende m&otilde;ju t&otilde;ttu transporditurgudel; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas a common approach allowing Member States to take joint measures toattain the same objective is a sine qua non for regulating capacity; whereas tothis end the scrapping funds introduced by Regulation (EEC) No 1101/89 in theMember States with inland waterways should be maintained, but under a newdesignation, and should administer this "old-for-new" rule; whereas the surplusfunds from the industry's contributions to structural improvement schemesconducted up until 28 April 1999 should be placed in a reserve fund attached tothe abovementioned funds; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) &uuml;lemahutavuse reguleerimise eelduseks on &uuml;hine l&auml;henemisviis, mis v&otilde;imaldab liikmesriikidel v&otilde;tta &uuml;hise eesm&auml;rgi saavutamiseks &uuml;hiseid meetmeid; selleks tuleks sisevetega liikmesriikides s&auml;ilitada m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1101/89 loodud vanametalliks lammutamise fondid, kuid uue nime all ja nii, et nende kaudu hallataks reeglit "vana uue vastu"; kuni 28. aprillini 1999 rakendatud struktuurit&auml;iustuskavade rahastamis&uuml;lej&auml;&auml;gid, mis on p&auml;rit t&ouml;&ouml;stusest saadud rahalistest toetusest, tuleks suunata eespool nimetatud fondide juurde kuuluvatesse reservfondidesse; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Whereas, in view of the fundamental differences between the dry cargo, liquid cargo and pusher craft markets, it is advisable to keep separateaccounts in each fund for dry cargo carriers, tanker vessels and pusher craft; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) silmas pidades kuiv- ja vedellasti ja t&otilde;kurpuksiirituru p&otilde;hierinevusi, on soovitatav pidada igas fondis eraldi arvet kuivlastilaevade, tankerite ja t&otilde;ukurpuksiiride kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Whereas, in the context of an economic policy compatible with the Treaty, responsibility for capacity regulation lies primarily with operators in thesector; whereas the cost of the measures introduced should therefore be borneby the undertakings in the inland waterway sector; whereas this capacityregulation consists of laying down the conditions to apply for bringing intoservice certain new capacity without going so far as totally blocking access tothe market; whereas it is possible to limit the duration and impact of theseconditions and to adjust them flexibly to market trends but the ratios mustgradually be reduced to zero within four years starting on 29 April 1999; whereas this regulatory mechanism designated the "old-for-new" rule should bemaintained as a standby mechanism once the ratio reaches zero; whereas thespecial contributions paid under the "old-for-new" rule should be placed in thereserve fund and may be used for granting scrapping premiums, if interventionin the market proves necessary; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) asutamislepinguga koosk&otilde;las olevas majanduspoliitikas lasub majanduse eri sektorite mahutavuse reguleerimise vastutus eelk&otilde;ige vastava sektori ettev&otilde;tjatel; seep&auml;rast peavad siseveetranspordi ettev&otilde;tjad kandma rakendatud meetmetega seotud kulud; see mahutavuse reguleerimine h&otilde;lmab niisuguste tingimuste kehtestamist, mida kohaldatakse teatava uue mahutavuse kasutuselev&otilde;tu suhtes, t&otilde;kestamata siiski t&auml;ielikult juurdep&auml;&auml;su asjaomasele turule; on v&otilde;imalik piirata nende tingimuste kestust ja m&otilde;ju ning kohandada neid paindlikult vastavalt turusuundumustele, kuid suhtarve tuleb nelja aasta jooksul alates 29. aprillist 1999 j&auml;rkj&auml;rgult v&auml;hendada kuni nullini; reguleerimismehhanismi, mida tuntakse reegli "vana uue vastu" nime all, tuleks s&auml;ilitada toetusmehhanismina seni, kuni suhtarv j&otilde;uab nullini; erilised osamaksud, mida makstakse vastavalt reeglile "vana uue vastu", tuleks suunata reservfondi ja neid v&otilde;ib kasutada vanametalliks lammutamise h&uuml;vitisteks, kui sekkumine sellel turul osutub vajalikuks; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Whereas it is desirable to ensure that the measures provided for in thisRegulation and implementation thereof do not distort, or threaten to distort, competition, in particular by favouring certain undertakings to an extent whichis contrary to the common interest; whereas, in order to place the enterprisesconcerned in similar conditions of competition, the special contributions to bepaid to the funds covering the building of new craft and the scrappingpremiums, if such premiums prove necessary in the event of a seriousdisturbance of the market and in accordance with the procedure provided for inArticle 8 of Directive 96/75/EC, should be set at uniform rates and on uniformterms; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) on soovitatav tagada, et k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed ja nende rakendamine ei moonutaks ega &auml;hvardaks moonutada konkurentsi, eriti eelistades teatavaid ettev&otilde;tjaid m&auml;&auml;ral, mis on vastuolus &uuml;histe huvidega; selleks et panna asjaomased ettev&otilde;tjad samadesse konkurentsitingimustesse, tuleks kehtestada &uuml;htsed m&auml;&auml;rad ja tingimused erilistele osamaksudele, mida tuleb maksta uute laevade ehitamise fondi, ja vanametalliks lammutamise h&uuml;vitistele, kui sellised h&uuml;vitised osutuvad direktiivi 96/75/E&Uuml; artiklis 8 kehtestatud korra kohaselt t&otilde;siste turuh&auml;irete korral vajalikuks; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Whereas, since the inland waterway fleets are Community fleets, decisionson operation of this capacity-regulation mechanism should be taken at Communitylevel; whereas the power to adopt such decisions, to see to implementationthereof and to safeguard the conditions of competition laid down in thisRegulation should be conferred on the Commission; whereas it is important thatthe Commission take such decisions after consulting the Member States and theorganisations representing inland waterway transport at Community level; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) kuna siseveeteede laevastikud on &uuml;henduse laevastikud, tuleks nende mahutavuse reguleerimise otsused vastu v&otilde;tta &uuml;henduse tasandil; volitused niisuguste otsuste vastuv&otilde;tmiseks ja rakendamiseks ja k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud konkurentsitingimuste tagamiseks tuleks anda komisjonile; on t&auml;htis, et komisjon v&otilde;taks need otsused vastu p&auml;rast konsulteerimist liikmesriikidega ja siseveetransporti &uuml;henduse tasandil esindavate organisatsioonidega; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) Whereas, in connection with the modernisation and restructuring of theCommunity fleets to create a context favourable to the environment and safety, social measures should be envisaged to help workers who wish to leave theinland waterway industry or to retrain for jobs in another sector, togetherwith measures to encourage the establishment of groupings of undertakings, toimprove operators' skills and to promote adaptation of the vessels to technicalprogress, </inglise>
<eesti> 9) seoses &uuml;henduse laevastiku moderniseerimise ja &uuml;mberkorraldamisega tuleks keskkonnakaitse ja ohutuse soodsate tingimuste seisukohast ette n&auml;ha sotsiaalmeetmed nende t&ouml;&ouml;tajate aitamiseks, kes soovivad siseveetranspordi sektorist lahkuda v&otilde;i &otilde;ppida &uuml;mber, et t&ouml;&ouml;tada muus sektoris, samuti meetmed, mis soodustaksid ettev&otilde;tjate r&uuml;hmituste loomist, mis parandaks ettev&otilde;tjate kutseoskusi ja edendaks laevade kohandamist vastavalt tehnika arengule, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Inland waterway vessels used to carry goods between two or more points byinland waterway in the Member States shall be subject to the Community-fleetcapacity policy laid down in this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud &uuml;henduse laevastiku mahutavuse poliitika kehtib siseveelaevade puhul, mida kasutatakse kaupade veol kahe v&otilde;i enama punkti vahel liikmesriikide siseveeteedel. </eesti>
<inglise> For a period of not more than four years with effect from 29 April 1999 thiscapacity policy shall include the conditions for bringing into service newcapacities, in accordance with this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> See mahutavuse poliitika sisaldab k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse alusel uute mahutavuste kasutuselev&otilde;tu tingimusi, mis kehtivad alates 29. aprillist 1999 k&otilde;ige enam nelja aasta jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall apply to cargo-carrying vessels and pusher craftproviding transport services on own account or for hire or reward andregistered in a Member State or, if not registered, operated by an undertakingestablished in a Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat m&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse kaubalaevade ja t&otilde;ukurpuksiiride suhtes, mis pakuvad veoteenuseid omal kulul v&otilde;i rendi v&otilde;i tasu eest ja mis on registreeritud m&otilde;nes liikmesriigis v&otilde;i mida kasutab, juhul kui neid ei ole registreeritud, m&otilde;nes liikmesriigis registrisse kantud ettev&otilde;tja. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Regulation, "undertaking" shall mean any natural orlegal person exercising an economic activity on a non-industrial or industrialscale. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses t&auml;hendab "ettev&otilde;tja" mis tahes f&uuml;&uuml;silist v&otilde;i juriidilist isikut, kes on h&otilde;ivatud t&ouml;&ouml;stusliku v&otilde;i mittet&ouml;&ouml;stusliku majandustegevusega. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The following shall be exempt from this Regulation: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat m&auml;&auml;rust ei kohaldata: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) vessels operating exclusively on national waterways not linked to otherwaterways in the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> a) laevade suhtes, mis s&otilde;idavad &uuml;ksnes siseriiklikel veeteedel, mis ei ole &uuml;henduses &uuml;henduse muude veeteedega; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) vessels which, owing to their dimensions, cannot leave the nationalwaterways on which they operate and cannot enter the other waterways of theCommunity (captive vessels), provided that such vessels are not likely tocompete with vessels covered by this Regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> b) laevade suhtes, mis ei saa oma m&otilde;&otilde;tmete t&otilde;ttu lahkuda siseriiklikelt veeteedelt, kus nad s&otilde;idavad, ega saa siseneda &uuml;henduse muudele veeteedele ("vanglaevad"), tingimusel et sellised laevad ei konkureeri k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse alla kuuluvate laevadega; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) vessels operating exclusively on the Danube (and its tributaries) up toKelheim without leaving it; </inglise>
<eesti> c) laevade suhtes, mis s&otilde;idavad eranditult Doonaul (ja selle lisaj&otilde;gedel) kuni Kelheimini sealt lahkumata; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) pusher craft with a motive power not exceeding 300 kilowatts; </inglise>
<eesti> d) t&otilde;ukurpuksiiride suhtes, mille liikumapanev j&otilde;ud ei &uuml;leta 300 kilovatti; </eesti>
<inglise> (e) sea-going inland waterway vessels and ship-borne barges used exclusivelyfor international or national transport operations during voyages which includea sea crossing; </inglise>
<eesti> e) merek&otilde;lblike siseveelaevade ja lihtrite suhtes, mida kasutatakse &uuml;ksnes rahvusvahelistel v&otilde;i siseriiklikel vedudel reiside puhul, mis sisaldavad merereisi; </eesti>
<inglise> (f) vessels used exclusively for storage of goods, i.e. vessels used forloading and subsequently unloading goods at the same place; </inglise>
<eesti> f) laevade suhtes, mida kasutataks eranditult ainult kaupade ladustamiseks, s.t laevad, mida kasutatakse &uuml;hes paigas kaupade laadimiseks ja mahalaadimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (g) dredging equipment, such as hopper vessels and pontoons and floatingconstruction plant, provided that such equipment is not used for the carriageof goods within the meaning of Article 1; </inglise>
<eesti> g) s&uuml;vendustehnika, n&auml;iteks punker-pinnasepraamide ja pontoonide ja pontoonidel ehitusmasinate suhtes, tingimusel et neid seadmeid ei kasutata kaupade veoks artikli 1 t&auml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise> (h) ferries; </inglise>
<eesti> h) parvlaevade suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise> (i) vessels providing a non-profit-making public service. </inglise>
<eesti> i) laevade suhtes, mis pakuvad avalikku teenust mittetulunduslikel eesm&auml;rkidel. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Each Member State concerned within the meaning of Article 3(1) may excludeits vessels with a deadweight tonnage of less than 450 tonnes from the scope ofthis Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;ik asjaomased liikmesriigid artikli 3 l&otilde;ike 1 t&auml;henduses, v&otilde;ivad k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse reguleerimisalast v&auml;lja j&auml;tta need oma laevad, mille dedveit tonnaa&zcaron; on alla 450 tonni. </eesti>
<inglise> Where a Member State avails itself of this option, it shallnotify the Commission accordingly within six months; the Commission shallinform the other Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriik kasutab seda v&otilde;imalust, teatab ta sellest komisjonile kuue kuu jooksul; komisjon teatab sellest teistele liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Each Member State whose inland waterways are linked to those of anotherMember State and the tonnage of whose fleet is above 100000 tonnes, hereinafterreferred to as "the Member State concerned", shall set up, under its nationallegislation and with its own administrative resources, an Inland WaterwaysFund, hereinafter referred to as "the Fund". </inglise>
<eesti> Iga liikmesriik, mille siseveeteed on &uuml;henduses m&otilde;ne teise liikmesriigi siseveeteedega ja mille laevastiku tonnaa&zcaron; on &uuml;le 100 000 tonni, edaspidi "asjaomased liikmesriigid", asutab oma siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide alusel ja oma haldusvahenditega siseveeteede fondi, edaspidi "fond". </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The competent authorities in the Member States concerned shall administerthe Fund. </inglise>
<eesti> Fondi rahastamist juhivad asjaomase liikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused. </eesti>
<inglise> Each Member State shall involve its national organisationsrepresenting inland waterway carriers in this administration. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga liikmesriik kaasab selle juhtimisse oma riigi siseveetranspordi ettev&otilde;tjaid esindavad riiklikud organisatsioonid. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Each Fund shall have a reserve fund consisting of three separate accounts; one for dry cargo carriers, one for tanker vessels and one for pusher craft. </inglise>
<eesti> Igal fondil on reservfond kolme eraldi kontoga: &uuml;ks kuivlastilaevadele, &uuml;ks tankeritele ja &uuml;ks t&otilde;ukurpuksiiridele. </eesti>
<inglise> This reserve fund shall be financed by: </inglise>
<eesti> Seda reservfondi rahastatakse: </eesti>
<inglise> - the surplus funding from the structural improvement schemes conducted upuntil 28 April 1999, consisting solely of financial contributions from theindustry, </inglise>
<eesti> - kuni 28. aprillini 1999 rakendatud struktuurit&auml;iustuskavade rahastamis&uuml;lej&auml;&auml;kidest, mis koosnevad &uuml;ksnes t&ouml;&ouml;stusest saadud rahalistest toetusest, </eesti>
<inglise> - the special contributions referred to in Article 4, </inglise>
<eesti> - artiklis 4 nimetatud erilisest rahalisest toetusest, </eesti>
<inglise> - the financial resources which could be made available in the event of seriousdisturbance of the market, as referred to in Article 7 of Directive 96/75/EC. </inglise>
<eesti> - rahalistest vahenditest, mida v&otilde;ib k&auml;ttesaadavaks teha direktiivi 96/75/E&Uuml; artiklis 7 nimetatud t&otilde;siste turuh&auml;irete korral. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The reserve fund may be used in connection with the suitable measuresreferred to in Article 7 of Directive 96/75/EC and, in particular, in thecourse of the improvement measures organised at Community level in accordancewith the procedure defined in paragraph 6 and Article 6 of the Regulation. </inglise>
